### ClickNBack — Workflow 1: Admin Platform Setup
###
### Goal: Create and activate a merchant, then create and activate an offer.
### Role: Admin
###
### Prerequisites:
###   - None. Use the demo admin account below, or replace with your own admin credentials.
###
### How to run:
###   1. Open this file in VS Code with the REST Client extension installed.
###   2. Run each request in order by clicking "Send Request" above each block.
###   3. Copy IDs from the responses into the variables below (or use REST Client's
###      request chaining — see comments on each step).
###
### Live API: https://clicknback.com
### Docs:     https://clicknback.com/docs

@baseUrl = https://clicknback.com


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 1 — Login as admin
#
# Expected: 200 OK with an access_token.
# Copy the access_token value and set @adminToken below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "carol@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}


###

# Set the token from step 1.
# In VS Code REST Client you can use: @adminToken = {{adminLogin.response.body.access_token}}
# Or paste the token manually after running the request above.
@adminToken = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 2 — Create a merchant
#
# Creates a new merchant in INACTIVE state (default).
# Expected: 201 Created with the new merchant's id.
# Copy the `id` value and set @merchantId below.
#
# Business rules:
#   - default_cashback_percentage is a fallback; actual cashback is driven by offers.
#   - The merchant starts inactive — it must be explicitly activated (step 3).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name createMerchant
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/merchants
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "Demo Store",
  "default_cashback_percentage": 5.0,
  "active": false
}


###

@merchantId = PASTE_MERCHANT_ID_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 3 — Activate the merchant
#
# Expected: 200 OK with id and status: "active".
# After this, the merchant appears in active merchant listings.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/merchants/{{merchantId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "active"
}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 4 — Create an offer for the merchant
#
# Creates a cashback offer starting today, valid for 30 days.
# Expected: 201 Created with the new offer's id and status: "inactive".
# Copy the `id` value and set @offerId below.
#
# Business rules:
#   - cashback_type: "percent" or "fixed"
#   - For "percent", cashback_value is the percentage (e.g., 5.0 = 5%)
#   - For "fixed", cashback_value is a monetary amount (e.g., 2.00 = €2.00)
#   - monthly_cap is the maximum cashback a user can earn from this offer per calendar month
#   - start_date must be today or a future date
#   - A merchant can have only ONE active offer at a time
#   - The offer starts inactive — it must be explicitly activated (step 5)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name createOffer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/offers
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "merchant_id": "{{merchantId}}",
  "cashback_type": "percent",
  "cashback_value": 5.0,
  "start_date": "2026-03-05",
  "end_date": "2026-04-05",
  "monthly_cap": 20.00
}


###

@offerId = PASTE_OFFER_ID_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 5 — Activate the offer
#
# Expected: 200 OK with id and status: "active".
# After this, the offer appears in GET /api/v1/offers/active for all logged-in users.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/offers/{{offerId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "active"
}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VERIFICATION — List merchants and confirm the new one appears
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/merchants?active=true&page=1&page_size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VERIFICATION — List all offers (admin view, paginated)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/offers?page=1&page_size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
